here are some feedbacks
1. The line-clearing logic could skip multiple lines if more than one full line exists, because it iterates top-down. Iterating bottom-up ensures all full lines are detected and cleared correctly.
2. The match detection never resets previous `matched` flags, which can lead to stale flags persisting between rounds.
3. It’s clearer if `find_matches` returns the number of matches found, allowing the main loop to drive the chain-reaction more straightforwardly.

